    <p>
     As you saw in previous sections, one way to change the energy of an object is to do work on it.  Work arises when a force acts on an object that is displaced.
    </p>
		
	
	<definition xml:id="def_work">
	<title>Work</title>
	<statement>
	<p>The <term>work</term> done by a single force <m>\vec{F}</m> on an object moving from <m>\vec{r}_i</m> to <m>\vec{r}_f</m><fn>along a path described by <m>\vec{dr}</m></fn> is: <me>W = \int_{\vec{r}_i}^{\vec{r}_f} {\vec{F} \cdot \vec{dr}}</me> </p>
	</statement>
	</definition>

